results.title: 7 Hours of Touhou-Music for Studying
results.description:
Actually, I made this for myself, but I thought, that some people might enjoy it aswell. If you have recommendations for songs, that might fit this video, please tell me in the comments.

I added Binaural Beats, with the Frequency 440 and 470 (Beta Wave), which will make it easier to Focus. This effect only occurs, when both ears listen seperatedly to each Frequence, so you should listen to this with headphones. The sinetones in the background are the frequencies, but most of the time, you won't even notice, it's there.

If you want to seperately download the Binaural Track, I have also uploaded it to MEGA: https://mega.nz/#!xhMy1TwR!CN06ltujmG4vef-OX760Ix88M1XYdh8tfTvxFSxQGuk
Feel free to use it for any video idea you have. It is an 200-208 Alpha Frequency, so it can be helpful for Learning or Focusing.
Binaural Frequencies could be used for music compilations, subliminals or ASMR. I have no problem if you use them, but if you can, tell me about your video, because I want to see it too!   :  )

Questions you might have:
Are Binaural Beats dangerous? 
No, unless you suffer from certain medical conditions, like epilepsy. Apart from that, Binaural Beats have a positive influence on the brain. If you have never listened to Binaural Beats before, you might feel a little dizzy, but won't be for long.

Sources:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binaural_beats#Binaural_beats_and_music
http://www.binauralbeats.de/haeufige-fragen (In German)

As the numbering suggested, this is the continuation of the previous Toho piano medley. The first half of this medley is essentially the same as the previous medley, with a couple of new tracks thrown in between to give this medley a better feeling. Similarly to prior medley, the timeline for each track won't be listed in the description due to similar reason.

results.title: Touhou Project Coverage on "Imagine-Nation" Program (NHK World)
results.description:
Touhou Project Coverage by Imagine-Nation program on NHK World, featuring a glimpse of the Digital Expo Event, ZUN Interview, and others.

Main Site: http://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/english/tv/imagine/
Show originally aired on 6/1/2015.
Recorded by kkcwkoh.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The overall coverage is pretty decent with a few glaring misinformation by the narrator. Explanations are done in a pretty basic manner to give the audience a general idea about the series.
Also quite glad to hear that ZUN is still sticking with his usual progression of the games; Music to Characters to Game progression.

Also to note at 2:26, the stream died for a brief moment due to an influx of visitors viewing the stream. Fortunately, it only happened once. From what I've heard, the missing parts basically talks about porting Touhou to consoles like PS4 and PS Vita.
